 twoSumLessThanK(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:\n        nums.sort()\n        left, right = 0, len(nums) - 1\n        max_sum = -1\n        \n        while left < right:\n            current_sum = nums[left] + nums[right]\n            if current_sum < k:\n                max_sum = max(max_sum, current_sum)\n                left += 1\n            else:\n                right -= 1\n        \n        return max_sum\n```\n\nThis solution sorts the array first and then uses a two-pointer technique to find the maximum sum of any two numbers that is less than `k`. The `left` pointer starts at the beginning of the array, and the `right` pointer starts at the end. If the sum of the numbers at these two pointers is less than `k`, it updates the `max_sum` and moves the `left` pointer to the right to try to find a larger sum. If the sum is greater than or equal to `k`, it moves the `right` pointer to the left to try to find a smaller sum. The process continues until the two pointers meet.", "estimated_date": 1561248000000}